{
    "name": "Talrepi Warden",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Kathrepi built talrepi wardens as brutally efficient guards. Kathrepi scientists understood that their experiments might spawn hostile test subjects or that forces dedicated to entropy in the universe might try to sabotage their research. They didn\u2019t consider, until the very end, that they might not need these guardians because their experiments would fail on their own. <br/>Although talrepi wardens tower over kathrepi, they aren\u2019t much taller than a human. Barrel-shaped with gangly arms ending in strong pincers, wardens grab targets and squeeze the life out of them. Like their kathrepi creators, wardens occupy four dimensions, but they lack their creators\u2019 ability to retreat into the fourth dimension for a long period of time. Instead, a warden can only make quick leaps into the fourth dimension.Talrepi wardens are designed to last for ages, though their components are susceptible to disruption by certain sonic frequencies. They still watch over the Tesseract even though nearly all kathrepi have vanished, and their long years of abandonment mean many wardens are stuck in the same routines and liable to be sent into a rampage by even by small variations in their otherwise unchanging environment."
        }
    ],
